(199, 1, '2017-05-09 06:50:20', '2017-05-09 06:50:20', 'You use Event Based Alerts to send custom messages to your users. Before you use this API you have to <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/tools/dashboard#event_based_alerts">Setup a Pre-approved Short Code for Event Based Alerts</a>\r\n\r\nThe workflow for sending Event Based Alerts is:\r\n<figure><img src="https://docs.nexmo.com/assets/images/workflow_sending_event_based_alerts.svg" alt="workflow_sending_event_based_alerts" /></figure>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Send an Event Based Alerts <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/messaging/us-short-codes-api/event-based-alerts/send-event-based-alerts/api-reference#request">request</a>.</li>\r\n 	<li>Check the <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/messaging/us-short-codes-api/event-based-alerts/send-event-based-alerts/api-reference#status-codes">response codes</a> in the <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/messaging/us-short-codes-api/event-based-alerts/send-event-based-alerts/api-reference#response">response</a> and ensure that you sent the request to Nexmo correctly.</li>\r\n 	<li>Nexmo sends the alert to your user.</li>\r\n 	<li>Receive the <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/messaging/us-short-codes-api/two-factor-authentication/api-reference#delivery-receipt">delivery receipt</a> at your <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/messaging/setup-callbacks">webhook endpoint</a> and verify delivery.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h2>Implementing the Event Based Alerts workflow</h2>\r\nTo send Event Based Alerts to your users:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Send an Event Based Alerts <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/messaging/us-short-codes-api/event-based-alerts/send-event-based-alerts/api-reference#request">request</a>. If you have multiple templates, remember to set the <i>template</i> number in your request.\r\n<ul class="nav nav-tabs">\r\n 	<li class="active"><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/messaging/us-short-codes-api/event-based-alerts/send-event-based-alerts#php" data-toggle="tab">PHP</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.ne