(226, 1, '2017-05-09 07:01:51', '2017-05-09 07:01:51', 'A Text-To-Speech <em>request</em> looks like:\r\n\r\n<code>https://api.nexmo.com/tts/json?api_key=xxxxxxxx&amp;api_secret=xxxxxxxx&amp;to=xxxxxxxxxxxx&amp;text="You are only, &lt;break time="1s"/&gt;24 hours from &lt;prosody rate="-20"&gt;Tulsa&lt;/prosody&gt;"</code>\r\n\r\nThis request contains:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/request#base">Base URL</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/request#parameters">Parameters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/request#authentic">Authentication information</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/request#security">Security</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/request#encode">Encoding</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a name="base"></a>\r\n<h2>Base URL</h2>\r\nAll requests to Call API must contain:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><code>https://api.nexmo.com/tts</code></li>\r\n 	<li>A response object: <em>json</em> or <em>xml</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nYour base URL becomes either:\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>JSON</th>\r\n<th>XML</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><code>https://api.nexmo.com/tts/json</code></td>\r\n<td><code>https://api.nexmo.com/tts/xml</code></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<a name="parameters"></a>\r\n<h2>Parameters</h2>\r\nThe following table shows the parameters you use in the request:\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Parameter</th>\r\n<th>Description</th>\r\n<th>Required</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>to</td>\r\n<td>The single phone number to call for each request. This number must be in <strong>international format</strong>, that is <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E.164">E.164</a>. For example, when sending to the uk: <em>to=447525856424</em>.</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>from</td>\r\n<td>A voice-enabled virtual number associated with your Nexmo account. This number is displayed on your user''s handset during this Text-To-Speech or Text-To-Speech Prompt. Check the <a href="https://help.nexmo.com/hc/en-us/sections/200637656-Country-Specific-Features-and-Restrictions" target="_blank">features and restrictions</a> to see if this is possible in your destination country.</td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>text</td>\r\n<td>A UTF-8 and URL encoded message that is sent to your user. This message can be up to 1500 characters). <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/tts-hints">Text-To-Speech Messages</a> explains how to control the pacing of your message.</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>lg</td>\r\n<td>The <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/supported-languages">language</a> used to synthesize the message. Combine this parameter with <em>voice</em> to control the language, accent and gender used to deliver this TTS. The default language is en-us.\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: ensure that <em>lg</em> matches the language you have written in <em>text</em>.</td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>voice</td>\r\n<td>The gender of the voice used for the TTS. Possible values are <em>female</em> or <em>male</em>. The default value is female.</td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>repeat</td>\r\n<td>Define how many times you want to repeat the text message. You can set a message to be repeated up to 10 times. The default is 1.</td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>machine_detection</td>\r\n<td>Control the way this TTS is handled if it is picked up by an answering machine. Set to:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>true</strong> — play the message after the beep. If the answerphone does not issue a beep the call is closed.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>hangup</strong> — hang up. The value of the <em>status</em> sent in the <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/status-codes">Text-To-Speech Return Parameters</a> is set to <em>machine</em>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>machine_timeout</td>\r\n<td>The time to check if this TTS has been answered by a machine. Possible values range from 400ms to the default value of 10000ms. If you set a number outside this range the <em>machine_timeout</em> is set to the default value.</td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>callback<a name="callback"></a></td>\r\n<td>Nexmo sends the <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/status-codes">Text-To-Speech Return Parameters</a> to this URL to tell your App how the call was executed.</td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>callback_method</td>\r\n<td>The HTTP method used to send the status message to your <em>callback</em>. Must be <em>GET</em> (default) or <em>POST</em>.</td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<a name="authentic"></a>\r\n<h3>Authentication information</h3>\r\nIf you are not using applications, you use the following parameters for calls to Nexmo API:\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Parameter</th>\r\n<th>Description</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>api_key</td>\r\n<td>Your Key. For example: <code>api_key=n3xm0rocks</code></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>api_secret</td>\r\n<td>Your Secret. For example: <code>api_secret=12ab34cd</code></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nYou find your <strong>Key</strong> and <strong>Secret</strong> in <a href="https://dashboard.nexmo.com/private/dashboard" target="_blank">Dashboard</a>.\r\n\r\nIf you are using signatures to verify your requests use:\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Parameter</th>\r\n<th>Description</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>api_key</td>\r\n<td>Your Key. For example: <code>api_key=n3xm0rocks</code></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>sig</td>\r\n<td>The hash of the request parameters in alphabetical order, a timestamp and the signature secret. For example: <code>sig=TwoMenWentToMowWentTOMowAMeadowT</code><a name="security"></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3>Security</h3>\r\nTo ensure privacy, you must use HTTPS for all Nexmo API requests.<a name="encode"></a>\r\n<h3>Encoding</h3>\r\nYou submit all requests with a <strong>POST</strong> or <strong>GET</strong> call using UTF-8 encoding and URL encoded values. The expected <strong>Content-Type</strong> for <strong>POST</strong> is <strong>application/x-www-form-urlencoded</strong>. For calls to a <strong>JSON</strong> endpoint, we also support:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>application/json</li>\r\n 	<li>application/jsonrequest</li>\r\n 	<li>application/x-javascript</li>\r\n 	<li>text/json</li>\r\n 	<li>text/javascript</li>\r\n 	<li>text/x-javascript</li>\r\n 	<li>text/x-json when posting parameters as a JSON object.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Request', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'request', '', '', '2017-05-09 07:01:51', '2017-05-09 07:01:51', '', 224, 'http://localhost:8080/Nexmo/Source/BE/?page_id=226', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(227, 1, '2017-05-09 07:01:51', '2017-05-09 07:01:51', 'A Text-To-Speech <em>request</em> looks like:\r\n\r\n<code>https://api.nexmo.com/tts/json?api_key=xxxxxxxx&amp;api_secret=xxxxxxxx&amp;to=xxxxxxxxxxxx&amp;text="You are only, &lt;break time="1s"/&gt;24 hours from &lt;prosody rate="-20"&gt;Tulsa&lt;/prosody&gt;"</code>\r\n\r\nThis request contains:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/request#base">Base URL</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/request#parameters">Parameters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/request#authentic">Authentication information</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/request#security">Security</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/request#encode">Encoding</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a name="base"></a>\r\n<h2>Base URL</h2>\r\nAll requests to Call API must contain:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><code>https://api.nexmo.com/tts</code></li>\r\n 	<li>A response object: <em>json</em> or <em>xml</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nYour base URL becomes either:\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>JSON</th>\r\n<th>XML</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><code>https://api.nexmo.com/tts/json</code></td>\r\n<td><code>https://api.nexmo.com/tts/xml</code></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<a name="parameters"></a>\r\n<h2>Parameters</h2>\r\nThe following table shows the parameters you use in the request:\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Parameter</th>\r\n<th>Description</th>\r\n<th>Required</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>to</td>\r\n<td>The single phone number to call for each request. This number must be in <strong>international format</strong>, that is <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E.164">E.164</a>. For example, when sending to the uk: <em>to=447525856424</em>.</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>from</td>\r\n<td>A voice-enabled virtual number associated with your Nexmo account. This number is displayed on your user''s handset during this Text-To-Speech or Text-To-Speech Prompt. Check the <a href="https://help.nexmo.com/hc/en-us/sections/200637656-Country-Specific-Features-and-Restrictions" target="_blank">features and restrictions</a> to see if this is possible in your destination country.</td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>text</td>\r\n<td>A UTF-8 and URL encoded message that is sent to your user. This message can be up to 1500 characters). <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/tts-hints">Text-To-Speech Messages</a> explains how to control the pacing of your message.</td>\r\n<td>Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>lg</td>\r\n<td>The <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/supported-languages">language</a> used to synthesize the message. Combine this parameter with <em>voice</em> to control the language, accent and gender used to deliver this TTS. The default language is en-us.\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: ensure that <em>lg</em> matches the language you have written in <em>text</em>.</td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>voice</td>\r\n<td>The gender of the voice used for the TTS. Possible values are <em>female</em> or <em>male</em>. The default value is female.</td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>repeat</td>\r\n<td>Define how many times you want to repeat the text message. You can set a message to be repeated up to 10 times. The default is 1.</td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>machine_detection</td>\r\n<td>Control the way this TTS is handled if it is picked up by an answering machine. Set to:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>true</strong> — play the message after the beep. If the answerphone does not issue a beep the call is closed.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>hangup</strong> — hang up. The value of the <em>status</em> sent in the <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/status-codes">Text-To-Speech Return Parameters</a> is set to <em>machine</em>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>machine_timeout</td>\r\n<td>The time to check if this TTS has been answered by a machine. Possible values range from 400ms to the default value of 10000ms. If you set a number outside this range the <em>machine_timeout</em> is set to the default value.</td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>callback<a name="callback"></a></td>\r\n<td>Nexmo sends the <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/status-codes">Text-To-Speech Return Parameters</a> to this URL to tell your App how the call was executed.</td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>callback_method</td>\r\n<td>The HTTP method used to send the status message to your <em>callback</em>. Must be <em>GET</em> (default) or <em>POST</em>.</td>\r\n<td>No</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<a name="authentic"></a>\r\n<h3>Authentication information</h3>\r\nIf you are not using applications, you use the following parameters for calls to Nexmo API:\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Parameter</th>\r\n<th>Description</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>api_key</td>\r\n<td>Your Key. For example: <code>api_key=n3xm0rocks</code></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>api_secret</td>\r\n<td>Your Secret. For example: <code>api_secret=12ab34cd</code></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nYou find your <strong>Key</strong> and <strong>Secret</strong> in <a href="https://dashboard.nexmo.com/private/dashboard" target="_blank">Dashboard</a>.\r\n\r\nIf you are using signatures to verify your requests use:\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Parameter</th>\r\n<th>Description</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>api_key</td>\r\n<td>Your Key. For example: <code>api_key=n3xm0rocks</code></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>sig</td>\r\n<td>The hash of the request parameters in alphabetical order, a timestamp and the signature secret. For example: <code>sig=TwoMenWentToMowWentTOMowAMeadowT</code><a name="security"></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3>Security</h3>\r\nTo ensure privacy, you must use HTTPS for all Nexmo API requests.<a name="encode"></a>\r\n<h3>Encoding</h3>\r\nYou submit all requests with a <strong>POST</strong> or <strong>GET</strong> call using UTF-8 encoding and URL encoded values. The expected <strong>Content-Type</strong> for <strong>POST</strong> is <strong>application/x-www-form-urlencoded</strong>. For calls to a <strong>JSON</strong> endpoint, we also support:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>application/json</li>\r\n 	<li>application/jsonrequest</li>\r\n 	<li>application/x-javascript</li>\r\n 	<li>text/json</li>\r\n 	<li>text/javascript</li>\r\n 	<li>text/x-javascript</li>\r\n 	<li>text/x-json when posting parameters as a JSON object.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Request', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '226-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-09 07:01:51', '2017-05-09 07:01:51', '', 226, 'http://localhost:8080/Nexmo/Source/BE/226-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(228, 1, '2017-05-09 07:02:26', '2017-05-09 07:02:26', 'Each <em>request</em> you make using the Text-To-Speech API and the Text-To-Speech Prompt API returns a:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/response#keys">Response</a> - the status of your request to Nexmo in <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/request#base">JSON or XML</a> format.</li>\r\n 	<li>If you set <em>callback</em> in your request, <em>Return Parameters</em> that explain the final status of this TTS or TTS Prompt are sent to your <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/messaging/setup-callbacks">webhook endpoint</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe response is send in the <em>api.txt</em> file when you make a request from the browser.\r\n\r\n<em>Note</em>: you are only charged for correctly submitted TTS. If <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/response#status">status</a> is not <code>0</code>, you are not charged.\r\n\r\nEach response comes:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>In a specific <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/response#format">Format</a></li>\r\n 	<li>With <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/response#keys">Keys and values</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a name="format"></a>\r\n<h2>Format</h2>\r\nYou set the response type using the <em>Base URL</em>. The following table shows example responses in JSON or XML:\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th width="50%">JSON</th>\r\n<th>XML</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<pre>{\r\n  "call_id":"${callId}",\r\n  "to":"${to}",\r\n  "status":"${status}",\r\n  "error_text":"${error_text}"\r\n}\r\n</pre>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<pre>&lt;?xml version=''1.0'' encoding=''UTF-8'' ?&gt;\r\n&lt;response&gt;\r\n  &lt;call_id&gt;${callId}&lt;/call_id&gt;\r\n  &lt;to&gt;${to}&lt;/to&gt;\r\n  &lt;status&gt;${status}&lt;/status&gt;\r\n  &lt;error_text&gt;${error_text}&lt;/error_text&gt;\r\n&lt;/response&gt;\r\n</pre>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<a name="keys"></a>\r\n<h2>Keys and Values</h2>\r\nThe response contains the following keys and values:<a name="response"></a>\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Key</th>\r\n<th>Value</th>\r\n<th>Response type</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>call_id</td>\r\n<td>A unique alphanumeric 32 character ID for this call.</td>\r\n<td>Both</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>to</td>\r\n<td>The phone number of the user you sent the TTS or TTS Prompt to.</td>\r\n<td>Both</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a name="status"></a>status</td>\r\n<td>The <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/response/response-codes">Response code</a> for this TTS or TTS Prompt.</td>\r\n<td>Both</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>error_text</td>\r\n<td>If the value of <em>status</em> is not 0, this explains the issue.</td>\r\n<td>Both</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'Response', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'response', '', '', '2017-05-09 07:02:26', '2017-05-09 07:02:26', '', 224, 'http://localhost:8080/Nexmo/Source/BE/?page_id=228', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(229, 1, '2017-05-09 07:02:26', '2017-05-09 07:02:26', 'Each <em>request</em> you make using the Text-To-Speech API and the Text-To-Speech Prompt API returns a:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/response#keys">Response</a> - the status of your request to Nexmo in <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/request#base">JSON or XML</a> format.</li>\r\n 	<li>If you set <em>callback</em> in your request, <em>Return Parameters</em> that explain the final status of this TTS or TTS Prompt are sent to your <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/messaging/setup-callbacks">webhook endpoint</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe response is send in the <em>api.txt</em> file when you make a request from the browser.\r\n\r\n<em>Note</em>: you are only charged for correctly submitted TTS. If <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/response#status">status</a> is not <code>0</code>, you are not charged.\r\n\r\nEach response comes:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>In a specific <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/response#format">Format</a></li>\r\n 	<li>With <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/response#keys">Keys and values</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a name="format"></a>\r\n<h2>Format</h2>\r\nYou set the response type using the <em>Base URL</em>. The following table shows example responses in JSON or XML:\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th width="50%">JSON</th>\r\n<th>XML</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<pre>{\r\n  "call_id":"${callId}",\r\n  "to":"${to}",\r\n  "status":"${status}",\r\n  "error_text":"${error_text}"\r\n}\r\n</pre>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<pre>&lt;?xml version=''1.0'' encoding=''UTF-8'' ?&gt;\r\n&lt;response&gt;\r\n  &lt;call_id&gt;${callId}&lt;/call_id&gt;\r\n  &lt;to&gt;${to}&lt;/to&gt;\r\n  &lt;status&gt;${status}&lt;/status&gt;\r\n  &lt;error_text&gt;${error_text}&lt;/error_text&gt;\r\n&lt;/response&gt;\r\n</pre>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<a name="keys"></a>\r\n<h2>Keys and Values</h2>\r\nThe response contains the following keys and values:<a name="response"></a>\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Key</th>\r\n<th>Value</th>\r\n<th>Response type</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>call_id</td>\r\n<td>A unique alphanumeric 32 character ID for this call.</td>\r\n<td>Both</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>to</td>\r\n<td>The phone number of the user you sent the TTS or TTS Prompt to.</td>\r\n<td>Both</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><a name="status"></a>status</td>\r\n<td>The <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech/response/response-codes">Response code</a> for this TTS or TTS Prompt.</td>\r\n<td>Both</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>error_text</td>\r\n<td>If the value of <em>status</em> is not 0, this explains the issue.</td>\r\n<td>Both</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'Response', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '228-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-09 07:02:26', '2017-05-09 07:02:26', '', 228, 'http://localhost:8080/Nexmo/Source/BE/228-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(230, 1, '2017-05-09 07:03:26', '2017-05-09 07:03:26', 'You use the following parameters to control the language, accent and gender a <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech">Text-To-Speech</a> or <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/voice/voice-deprecated/text-to-speech-prompt">Text-To-Speech Prompt</a> is delivered in:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>lg - the language and accent used in the TTS. For example, fr-ca would be a message in French spoken with a Canadian accent.</li>\r\n 	<li>voice - the gender of the voice used for the TTS. Possible values are <em>female</em> or <em>male</em>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: the default <em>voice</em> is female.\r\n\r\nThese languages are also supported for VoiceXML. For example:\r\n<code>&lt;prompt xml:lang="es-mx-female"&gt;</code>\r\n\r\nThe following table shows the possible <em>lg</em> and <em>voice</em> combinations:\r\n<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Value</th>\r\n<th>Language-Accent</th>\r\n<th>Available Voices</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>de-de</td>\r\n<td>German, German</td>\r\n<td>female / male</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>en-au</td>\r\n<td>English, Australian</td>\r\n<td>female / male</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>en-gb</td>\r\n<td>English, UK</td>\r\n<td>female / male</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>en-us (default)</td>\r\n<td>English, US</td>\r\n<td>female / male</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>en-in</td>\r\n<td>English, Indian</td>\r\n<td>female</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>es-es</td>\r\n<td>Spanish, Spanish</td>\r\n<td>female / male</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>es-mx</td>\r\n<td>Spanish, Mexican</td>\r\n<td>female</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>es-us</td>\r\n<td>Spanish, US</td>\r\n<td>female / male</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>fr-ca</td>\r\n<td>French, Canadian</td>\r\n<td>female</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>fr-fr</td>\r\n<td>French, French</td>\r\n<td>female / male</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>is-is</td>\r\n<td>Icelandic, Icelandic</td>\r\n<td>female / male</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>it-it</td>\r\n<td>Italian, Italian</td>\r\n<td>female / male</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>ja-jp</td>\r\n<td>Japanese, Japanese</td>\r\n<td>female / male</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>ko-kr</td>\r\n<td>Korean, Korean</td>\r\n<td>female / male</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>nl-nl</td>\r\n<td>Dutch, Netherlands</td>\r\n<td>female / male</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>pl-pl</td>\r\n<td>Polish, Polish</td>\r\n<td>female / male</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>pt-pt</td>\r\n<td>Portuguese, Portuguese</td>\r\n<td>male</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>pt-br</td>\r\n<td>Portuguese, Brazilian</td>\r\n<td>female / male</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>ro-ro</td>\r\n<td>Romanian, Romanian</td>\r\n<td>female</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>ru-ru</td>\r\n<td>Russian, Russian</td>\r\n<td>female</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>sv-se</td>\r\n<td>Swedish, Sweden</td>\r\n<td>female</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>tr-tr</td>\r\n<td>Turkish, Turkish</td>\r\n<td>female</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>zh-cn</td>\r\n<td>Chinese (Mandarin), Chinese</td>\r\n<td>female / male</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: the default <em>voice</em> is always female.', 'Language, accent and gender', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'language-accent-and-gender', '', '', '2017-05-09 07:03:26', '2017-05-09 07:03:26', '', 204, 'http://localhost:8080/Nexmo/Source/BE/?page_id=230', 0, 'page', '', 0),
