(242, 1, '2017-05-09 07:11:50', '2017-05-09 07:11:50', '<h1></h1>\r\nUsing Verify SDK for Android, you integrate Verify functionality directly into your Android App:\r\n\r\nTo do this:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-android/prerequisites">Setup your environment</a>.</li>\r\n 	<li>Add the following items to your Manifest so Verify SDK can access the device id, internet and network connection for your users handset:\r\n<pre><code class="hljs xml"><span class="hljs-comment">&lt;!-- Automatically granted permissions PROTECTION_NORMAL --&gt;</span>\r\n<span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">uses-permission</span> <span class="hljs-attr">android:name</span>=<span class="hljs-string">"android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE"</span>/&gt;</span>\r\n<span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">uses-permission</span> <span class="hljs-attr">android:name</span>=<span class="hljs-string">"android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE"</span>/&gt;</span>\r\n<span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">uses-permission</span> <span class="hljs-attr">android:name</span>=<span class="hljs-string">"android.permission.INTERNET"</span>/&gt;</span>\r\n<span class="hljs-comment">&lt;!-- Permission has to be GRANTED --&gt;</span>\r\n<span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">uses-permission</span> <span class="hljs-attr">android:name</span>=<span class="hljs-string">"android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE"</span>/&gt;</span></code></pre>\r\nVerify SDK supports Android Marshmallow. The SDK handles runtime permissions, applications running on Marshmallow failover gracefully if your user denies permissions.</li>\r\n 	<li>Create a new Nexmo Client:\r\n<pre><code class="language-java hljs">Context context = getApplicationContext();\r\n<span class="hljs-keyword">try</span> {\r\n    NexmoClient nexmoClient = <span class="hljs-keyword">new</span> NexmoClient.NexmoClientBuilder()\r\n    .context(context)\r\n    .applicationId(MY_APP_ID) <span class="hljs-comment">//your App key</span>\r\n    .sharedSecretKey(MY_APP_SHARED_SECRET) <span class="hljs-comment">//your App secret</span>\r\n    .build();\r\n} <span class="hljs-keyword">catch</span> (ClientBuilderException e) {\r\n    e.printStackTrace();\r\n}</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Instantiate a new <em>VerifyClient</em>.\r\n<pre><code class="language-java hljs">verifyClient = <span class="hljs-keyword">new</span> VerifyClient(nexmoClient);</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Register a <em>Listener</em>. This is so your UI interacts with user events:\r\n<pre><code class="language-java hljs">verifyClient.addVerifyListener(<span class="hljs-keyword">new</span> VerifyClientListener() {\r\n<span class="hljs-meta">@Override</span>\r\n<span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">void</span> <span class="hljs-title">onVerifyInProgress</span><span class="hljs-params">(<span class="hljs-keyword">final</span> VerifyClient verifyClient, UserObject user)</span> </span>{\r\n    Log.d(TAG, <span class="hljs-string">"onVerifyInProgress for number: "</span> + user.getPhoneNumber());\r\n}\r\n\r\n<span class="hljs-meta">@Override</span>\r\n<span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">void</span> <span class="hljs-title">onUserVerified</span><span class="hljs-params">(<span class="hljs-keyword">final</span> VerifyClient verifyClient, UserObject user)</span> </span>{\r\n    Log.d(TAG, <span class="hljs-string">"onUserVerified for number: "</span> + user.getPhoneNumber());\r\n}\r\n\r\n<span class="hljs-meta">@Override</span>\r\n<span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">void</span> <span class="hljs-title">onError</span><span class="hljs-params">(<span class="hljs-keyword">final</span> VerifyClient verifyClient, <span class="hljs-keyword">final</span> com.nexmo.sdk.verify.event.VerifyError errorCode, UserObject user)</span> </span>{\r\n    Log.d(TAG, <span class="hljs-string">"onError: "</span> + errorCode + <span class="hljs-string">" for number: "</span> + user.getPhoneNumber());\r\n}\r\n\r\n<span class="hljs-meta">@Override</span>\r\n<span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">void</span> <span class="hljs-title">onException</span><span class="hljs-params">(<span class="hljs-keyword">final</span> IOException exception)</span> </span>{\r\n}\r\n});</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Instantiate a default verification, using your own UI components to handle phone number and PIN inputs:\r\n<pre><code class="language-java hljs">verifyClient.getVerifiedUser(<span class="hljs-string">"GB"</span>, <span class="hljs-string">"07000000000"</span>);</code></pre>\r\nEven if a user enters the phone number with the country code, Verify SDK for Android determines the correctly internationalized phone number.</li>\r\n 	<li>The user tries to verify a phone number in the App:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>If verification has started: <em>VerifyClientListener.onVerifyInProgress(final VerifyClient verifyClient, UserObject user)</em> is invoked.</li>\r\n 	<li>If verification cannot be started: <em>VerifyClientListener.onError(final VerifyClient verifyClient, final com.nexmo.sdk.verify.event.VerifyError errorCode, UserObject user)</em> is invoked to describe the error.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Supply the PIN entered by the user to the <em>VerifyClient</em> instance in your App:\r\n<pre><code class="language-java hljs">verifyClient.checkPinCode(<span class="hljs-string">"1234"</span>);</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>The <em>VerifyClientListener.onUserVerified(final VerifyClient verifyClient, UserObject user)</em> event is invoked when verification is successful.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: never store sensitive user details like the phone number locally. Persisting user information in local storage is not good user security.', 'Integrating Verify SDK for Android', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'integrating-verify-sdk-for-android', '', '', '2017-05-09 07:11:50', '2017-05-09 07:11:50', '', 238, 'http://localhost:8080/Nexmo/Source/BE/?page_id=242', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(243, 1, '2017-05-09 07:11:50', '2017-05-09 07:11:50', '<h1></h1>\r\nUsing Verify SDK for Android, you integrate Verify functionality directly into your Android App:\r\n\r\nTo do this:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-android/prerequisites">Setup your environment</a>.</li>\r\n 	<li>Add the following items to your Manifest so Verify SDK can access the device id, internet and network connection for your users handset:\r\n<pre><code class="hljs xml"><span class="hljs-comment">&lt;!-- Automatically granted permissions PROTECTION_NORMAL --&gt;</span>\r\n<span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">uses-permission</span> <span class="hljs-attr">android:name</span>=<span class="hljs-string">"android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE"</span>/&gt;</span>\r\n<span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">uses-permission</span> <span class="hljs-attr">android:name</span>=<span class="hljs-string">"android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE"</span>/&gt;</span>\r\n<span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">uses-permission</span> <span class="hljs-attr">android:name</span>=<span class="hljs-string">"android.permission.INTERNET"</span>/&gt;</span>\r\n<span class="hljs-comment">&lt;!-- Permission has to be GRANTED --&gt;</span>\r\n<span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">uses-permission</span> <span class="hljs-attr">android:name</span>=<span class="hljs-string">"android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE"</span>/&gt;</span></code></pre>\r\nVerify SDK supports Android Marshmallow. The SDK handles runtime permissions, applications running on Marshmallow failover gracefully if your user denies permissions.</li>\r\n 	<li>Create a new Nexmo Client:\r\n<pre><code class="language-java hljs">Context context = getApplicationContext();\r\n<span class="hljs-keyword">try</span> {\r\n    NexmoClient nexmoClient = <span class="hljs-keyword">new</span> NexmoClient.NexmoClientBuilder()\r\n    .context(context)\r\n    .applicationId(MY_APP_ID) <span class="hljs-comment">//your App key</span>\r\n    .sharedSecretKey(MY_APP_SHARED_SECRET) <span class="hljs-comment">//your App secret</span>\r\n    .build();\r\n} <span class="hljs-keyword">catch</span> (ClientBuilderException e) {\r\n    e.printStackTrace();\r\n}</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Instantiate a new <em>VerifyClient</em>.\r\n<pre><code class="language-java hljs">verifyClient = <span class="hljs-keyword">new</span> VerifyClient(nexmoClient);</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Register a <em>Listener</em>. This is so your UI interacts with user events:\r\n<pre><code class="language-java hljs">verifyClient.addVerifyListener(<span class="hljs-keyword">new</span> VerifyClientListener() {\r\n<span class="hljs-meta">@Override</span>\r\n<span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">void</span> <span class="hljs-title">onVerifyInProgress</span><span class="hljs-params">(<span class="hljs-keyword">final</span> VerifyClient verifyClient, UserObject user)</span> </span>{\r\n    Log.d(TAG, <span class="hljs-string">"onVerifyInProgress for number: "</span> + user.getPhoneNumber());\r\n}\r\n\r\n<span class="hljs-meta">@Override</span>\r\n<span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">void</span> <span class="hljs-title">onUserVerified</span><span class="hljs-params">(<span class="hljs-keyword">final</span> VerifyClient verifyClient, UserObject user)</span> </span>{\r\n    Log.d(TAG, <span class="hljs-string">"onUserVerified for number: "</span> + user.getPhoneNumber());\r\n}\r\n\r\n<span class="hljs-meta">@Override</span>\r\n<span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">void</span> <span class="hljs-title">onError</span><span class="hljs-params">(<span class="hljs-keyword">final</span> VerifyClient verifyClient, <span class="hljs-keyword">final</span> com.nexmo.sdk.verify.event.VerifyError errorCode, UserObject user)</span> </span>{\r\n    Log.d(TAG, <span class="hljs-string">"onError: "</span> + errorCode + <span class="hljs-string">" for number: "</span> + user.getPhoneNumber());\r\n}\r\n\r\n<span class="hljs-meta">@Override</span>\r\n<span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">void</span> <span class="hljs-title">onException</span><span class="hljs-params">(<span class="hljs-keyword">final</span> IOException exception)</span> </span>{\r\n}\r\n});</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Instantiate a default verification, using your own UI components to handle phone number and PIN inputs:\r\n<pre><code class="language-java hljs">verifyClient.getVerifiedUser(<span class="hljs-string">"GB"</span>, <span class="hljs-string">"07000000000"</span>);</code></pre>\r\nEven if a user enters the phone number with the country code, Verify SDK for Android determines the correctly internationalized phone number.</li>\r\n 	<li>The user tries to verify a phone number in the App:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>If verification has started: <em>VerifyClientListener.onVerifyInProgress(final VerifyClient verifyClient, UserObject user)</em> is invoked.</li>\r\n 	<li>If verification cannot be started: <em>VerifyClientListener.onError(final VerifyClient verifyClient, final com.nexmo.sdk.verify.event.VerifyError errorCode, UserObject user)</em> is invoked to describe the error.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>Supply the PIN entered by the user to the <em>VerifyClient</em> instance in your App:\r\n<pre><code class="language-java hljs">verifyClient.checkPinCode(<span class="hljs-string">"1234"</span>);</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>The <em>VerifyClientListener.onUserVerified(final VerifyClient verifyClient, UserObject user)</em> event is invoked when verification is successful.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: never store sensitive user details like the phone number locally. Persisting user information in local storage is not good user security.', 'Integrating Verify SDK for Android', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '242-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-09 07:11:50', '2017-05-09 07:11:50', '', 242, 'http://localhost:8080/Nexmo/Source/BE/242-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(244, 1, '2017-05-09 07:12:46', '2017-05-09 07:12:46', 'The Verify SDK for Android sample app shows you how to implement Verify SDK for Android into a mobile App.\r\n\r\nTo use this sample:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-android/verify-sample#import">Importing the sample app</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-android/verify-sample#run">Running the sample app</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<a name="import"></a>\r\n<h2>Importing the sample app</h2>\r\nTo use the Verify SDK for Android Sample App:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-android/prerequisites#prereq">Configure your Verify SDK App</a>.</li>\r\n 	<li>Clone Verify SDK for Android locally from: <a href="https://github.com/Nexmo/verify-android-sdk">https://github.com/Nexmo/verify-android-sdk</a>\r\n<code>git clone https://github.com/Nexmo/verify-android-sdk.git</code></li>\r\n 	<li>Open Android Studio.</li>\r\n 	<li>In the Welcome page, click <em>Import project</em>.</li>\r\n 	<li>In <em>Select Gradle Project to Import</em>, navigate to <em>&lt;git_home&gt;/verify-android-sdk/VerifySample</em> and click <em>OK</em>.</li>\r\n 	<li>If your project shows an error, install the tools suggested in <em>Messages</em> by Android Studio. Android Studio builds the project.</li>\r\n 	<li>Set your <strong>ID</strong> and <strong>Shared Secret</strong> in <em>app/java/com.nexmo.sdk.sample.verifysample/Config</em>:\r\n<pre><code class="hljs java"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">static</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">final</span> String NexmoAppId = <span class="hljs-string">"yourAppId"</span>;\r\n<span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">static</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">final</span> String NexmoSharedSecretKey = <span class="hljs-string">"YourSharedSecretKey"</span>;</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: this is a sample, you should persist this information on your App.\r\n\r\n<a name="run"></a>\r\n<h2>Running the sample app</h2>\r\nTo run this sample app:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Setup your mobile device to work with Android Studio: <a href="https://developer.android.com/tools/building/building-studio.html#RunningOnDeviceStudio">https://developer.android.com/tools/building/building-studio.html#RunningOnDeviceStudio</a>.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click <em>Run</em> &gt; <em>Run</em>, then select your mobile device.</li>\r\n 	<li>Follow the instructions in the App.</li>\r\n</ol>', 'The Verify SDK for Android sample app', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-verify-sdk-for-android-sample-app', '', '', '2017-05-09 07:12:46', '2017-05-09 07:12:46', '', 238, 'http://localhost:8080/Nexmo/Source/BE/?page_id=244', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(245, 1, '2017-05-09 07:12:46', '2017-05-09 07:12:46', 'The Verify SDK for Android sample app shows you how to implement Verify SDK for Android into a mobile App.\r\n\r\nTo use this sample:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-android/verify-sample#import">Importing the sample app</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-android/verify-sample#run">Running the sample app</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<a name="import"></a>\r\n<h2>Importing the sample app</h2>\r\nTo use the Verify SDK for Android Sample App:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-android/prerequisites#prereq">Configure your Verify SDK App</a>.</li>\r\n 	<li>Clone Verify SDK for Android locally from: <a href="https://github.com/Nexmo/verify-android-sdk">https://github.com/Nexmo/verify-android-sdk</a>\r\n<code>git clone https://github.com/Nexmo/verify-android-sdk.git</code></li>\r\n 	<li>Open Android Studio.</li>\r\n 	<li>In the Welcome page, click <em>Import project</em>.</li>\r\n 	<li>In <em>Select Gradle Project to Import</em>, navigate to <em>&lt;git_home&gt;/verify-android-sdk/VerifySample</em> and click <em>OK</em>.</li>\r\n 	<li>If your project shows an error, install the tools suggested in <em>Messages</em> by Android Studio. Android Studio builds the project.</li>\r\n 	<li>Set your <strong>ID</strong> and <strong>Shared Secret</strong> in <em>app/java/com.nexmo.sdk.sample.verifysample/Config</em>:\r\n<pre><code class="hljs java"><span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">static</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">final</span> String NexmoAppId = <span class="hljs-string">"yourAppId"</span>;\r\n<span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">static</span> <span class="hljs-keyword">final</span> String NexmoSharedSecretKey = <span class="hljs-string">"YourSharedSecretKey"</span>;</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: this is a sample, you should persist this information on your App.\r\n\r\n<a name="run"></a>\r\n<h2>Running the sample app</h2>\r\nTo run this sample app:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Setup your mobile device to work with Android Studio: <a href="https://developer.android.com/tools/building/building-studio.html#RunningOnDeviceStudio">https://developer.android.com/tools/building/building-studio.html#RunningOnDeviceStudio</a>.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click <em>Run</em> &gt; <em>Run</em>, then select your mobile device.</li>\r\n 	<li>Follow the instructions in the App.</li>\r\n</ol>', 'The Verify SDK for Android sample app', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '244-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-09 07:12:46', '2017-05-09 07:12:46', '', 244, 'http://localhost:8080/Nexmo/Source/BE/244-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(246, 1, '2017-05-09 07:13:17', '2017-05-09 07:13:17', 'Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) is the new version of Google Cloud Messaging (GCM) under the Firebase brand. It inherits GCM’s core infrastructure and adds new SDKs that make it easier for you to add mobile notifications to your app.\r\n\r\nFCM push notifications:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Are available after you have verified each user with SMS or Text-To-Speech.</li>\r\n 	<li>Are always sent to devices, not phone numbers. Using FCM, PINs are still delivered if your user changes SIM on their device.</li>\r\n 	<li>Work when a device has a data connection and is configured to accept incoming push notifications.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTo configure your Nexmo App for FCM:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Add Firebase to your Android project: <a href="https://firebase.google.com/docs/android/setup">https://firebase.google.com/docs/android/setup</a>.</li>\r\n 	<li>Provision your server key in Dashboard: <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-android/prerequisites#prereq">Configure your Verify SDK App</a>.</li>\r\n 	<li>In Android Studio, add the FCM dependency to your app-level <em>build.gradle</em>:\r\n<pre><code class="language-java hljs">dependencies {\r\ncompile <span class="hljs-string">''com.google.firebase:firebase-messaging:9.8.0''</span>\r\n}</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>In your app manifest, edit your service so that <em>FirebaseInstanceIdService</em> can create, rotate and update registration tokens. Make sure your app handles the refresh tokens and updates <em>nexmoClient</em>.\r\n<pre><code class="language-java hljs">nexmoClient.setPushRegistrationToken(<span class="hljs-string">"MyFirebaseRegistrationToken"</span>);</code></pre>\r\nThe registration token may change when:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The app deletes the Instance ID</li>\r\n 	<li>The app is restored on a new device</li>\r\n 	<li>The user uninstalls or reinstall the app</li>\r\n 	<li>The user clears app data</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: never store sensitive user details such as a phone number locally. Persisting user information in local storage is not good user security.', 'Configuring Firebase Cloud Messaging', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'configuring-firebase-cloud-messaging', '', '', '2017-05-09 07:13:17', '2017-05-09 07:13:17', '', 238, 'http://localhost:8080/Nexmo/Source/BE/?page_id=246', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(247, 1, '2017-05-09 07:13:17', '2017-05-09 07:13:17', 'Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) is the new version of Google Cloud Messaging (GCM) under the Firebase brand. It inherits GCM’s core infrastructure and adds new SDKs that make it easier for you to add mobile notifications to your app.\r\n\r\nFCM push notifications:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Are available after you have verified each user with SMS or Text-To-Speech.</li>\r\n 	<li>Are always sent to devices, not phone numbers. Using FCM, PINs are still delivered if your user changes SIM on their device.</li>\r\n 	<li>Work when a device has a data connection and is configured to accept incoming push notifications.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTo configure your Nexmo App for FCM:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Add Firebase to your Android project: <a href="https://firebase.google.com/docs/android/setup">https://firebase.google.com/docs/android/setup</a>.</li>\r\n 	<li>Provision your server key in Dashboard: <a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-android/prerequisites#prereq">Configure your Verify SDK App</a>.</li>\r\n 	<li>In Android Studio, add the FCM dependency to your app-level <em>build.gradle</em>:\r\n<pre><code class="language-java hljs">dependencies {\r\ncompile <span class="hljs-string">''com.google.firebase:firebase-messaging:9.8.0''</span>\r\n}</code></pre>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li>In your app manifest, edit your service so that <em>FirebaseInstanceIdService</em> can create, rotate and update registration tokens. Make sure your app handles the refresh tokens and updates <em>nexmoClient</em>.\r\n<pre><code class="language-java hljs">nexmoClient.setPushRegistrationToken(<span class="hljs-string">"MyFirebaseRegistrationToken"</span>);</code></pre>\r\nThe registration token may change when:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The app deletes the Instance ID</li>\r\n 	<li>The app is restored on a new device</li>\r\n 	<li>The user uninstalls or reinstall the app</li>\r\n 	<li>The user clears app data</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: never store sensitive user details such as a phone number locally. Persisting user information in local storage is not good user security.', 'Configuring Firebase Cloud Messaging', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '246-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-09 07:13:17', '2017-05-09 07:13:17', '', 246, 'http://localhost:8080/Nexmo/Source/BE/246-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(248, 1, '2017-05-09 07:14:53', '2017-05-09 07:14:53', 'You use Verify SDK for iOS to add password replacement, 2-factor authentication, or user and transaction verification to a native iOS App. With Verify SDK for iOS, you enter your user''s phone number and the SDK completes verification for you. Default verification is against <em>App Id + Device ID + Phone number</em>.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-iOS/prerequisites">Setup up your environment</a>: before you start coding, create a Verify SDK app in Dashboard and configure XCode.</li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-iOS/integration">Integrate Verify SDK for iOS</a>: create and run your first app.</li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-iOS/verify-sample">Verify SDK for iOS sample app</a>: integrate and run a more complete app.</li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-iOS/integrating-push">Configure Push notifications</a>: create and use APNS in your app.</li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-iOS/verify-push-sample">Verify SDK for iOS push enabled sample app</a>: integrate and run a more complete app with APNS.</li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-iOS/advanced">Verify SDK for iOS, advanced use</a>: use the advanced features in Verify SDK for iOS.</li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-iOS/example-configurations">Example configurations</a>: configurations for different types of app.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: Verify SDK for iOS supports iOS version 8.0 and above.', 'Verify SDK for iOS', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'verify-sdk-for-ios', '', '', '2017-05-09 07:14:53', '2017-05-09 07:14:53', '', 232, 'http://localhost:8080/Nexmo/Source/BE/?page_id=248', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(249, 1, '2017-05-09 07:14:53', '2017-05-09 07:14:53', 'You use Verify SDK for iOS to add password replacement, 2-factor authentication, or user and transaction verification to a native iOS App. With Verify SDK for iOS, you enter your user''s phone number and the SDK completes verification for you. Default verification is against <em>App Id + Device ID + Phone number</em>.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-iOS/prerequisites">Setup up your environment</a>: before you start coding, create a Verify SDK app in Dashboard and configure XCode.</li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-iOS/integration">Integrate Verify SDK for iOS</a>: create and run your first app.</li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-iOS/verify-sample">Verify SDK for iOS sample app</a>: integrate and run a more complete app.</li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-iOS/integrating-push">Configure Push notifications</a>: create and use APNS in your app.</li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-iOS/verify-push-sample">Verify SDK for iOS push enabled sample app</a>: integrate and run a more complete app with APNS.</li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-iOS/advanced">Verify SDK for iOS, advanced use</a>: use the advanced features in Verify SDK for iOS.</li>\r\n 	<li><a href="https://docs.nexmo.com/verify/verify-sdk-for-iOS/example-configurations">Example configurations</a>: configurations for different types of app.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Note</strong>: Verify SDK for iOS supports iOS version 8.0 and above.', 'Verify SDK for iOS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '248-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-05-09 07:14:53', '2017-05-09 07:14:53', '', 248, 'http://localhost:8080/Nexmo/Source/BE/248-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
